After you have driven the flaky tests out in the open, document every flaky test in your ticketing system. Flakiness related to concurrency can be caused by non-deterministic behaviour of the test, or the code under test. In some cases, there is a bug in the code. In others, the problem is that the code can produce different valid results, and the test accepts only one. This problem can be solved by making the test more robust, so that it accepts all valid results.
